channel.title: Need help with models
channel.description:
Dear people, Everytime i try to add a model i: -copy paste the models to my models folder. -add the file to class8. -press "add models"
But, everytime i log in, and i spawn the item it gives a Null. What to do?

item.title: Need help with models
item.dc:creator: @Thetwistedsnake Thetwistedsnake
item.description:
@Thetwistedsnake wrote:

[quote=“n00bf0rlyf3, post:6, topic:362261”][quote author=Thetwistedsnake link=topic=458547.msg3355531#msg3355531 date=1285797247]

Dear people,
Everytime i try to add a model i:
-copy paste the models to my models folder.
-add the file to class8.
-press “add models”

But, everytime i log in, and i spawn the item it gives a Null.
What to do?

1.When you download your models extract dont copy&paste (might fix)
2.Add ints to class 8 not files(copy and paste)
3.Go on client type ‘add models’ or ‘add model ####’ (no :: ) (If it doesnt work try no spaces)
4.Your models might me broken or something…
[size=18pt]LAST BUT NOT LEAST “WORNG SECTION”[/size]
[/quote]

You can C and P it the models… That wont change anything really. but if u do ‘add model’ u gotta do ‘::add model @@@@@’ @@@@@ = id number. for ‘add models’ dont do ::[/quote]
Dude your saying excatley like i said just “You can C and P it the models… That wont change anything really.”

Read full topic
